.Dd January 30, 2015
.Dt RM 1 sbase\-VERSION
.Sh NAME
.Nm rm
.Nd remove directory entries
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm rm
.Op Fl f | Fl i
.Op Fl Rr
.Ar file ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
removes each
.Ar file .
If
.Ar file
is a directory, it has to be empty unless
.Fl R
or
.Fl r
is specified.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl f | Fl i
Do not prompt | Prompt before removing
.Ar file .
In the former case, do not report when
.Ar file
doesn't exist or couldn't be removed.
.It Fl Rr
Remove directories recursively.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr remove 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
utility is compliant with the
.St -p1003.1-2008
specification except from prompting.
